# Continuously monitor subject's eye movements for smooth pursuit and stream status.
# Action server: eyelink node (nodes/eyelink.py, action ~/smooth_pursuit).
# Action client: EyelinkInterface.smooth_pursuit() (interfaces/eyelink.py).

# --- Goal (no fields; accepting the goal starts monitoring) ---
---
# --- Result (no fields; action is typically cancelled by the client when no longer needed) ---
---
# --- Feedback ---
# Whether smooth pursuit started or ended
bool is_smoothly_pursuing  # True if the subject's eyes are currently following a smoothly moving target (speed within configured min/max bounds); False if fixating or saccading
